Package com.rb.nonbiz.collections

Class RBDoubleKeyedMap<V>

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.collections.RBDoubleKeyedMap<V>
public class RBDoubleKeyedMap<V>
extends java.lang.Object
A map from a double to a value.

We can't use RBMap for this. In general, it's a bad idea to use doubles as keys, because double equality can be approximate in case a number is the result of a calculation (e.g. 0.8 is not the same as 0.2 * 0.4), so behavior can be unexpected.

This special map lets you look up values an 'almost equal' keys, subject to an epsilon.

Unlike MutableRBDoubleKeyedMap, this is immutable.
